Starboard Studios #game-news BOT 24-Sep-21 05:13 PM
Hi everyone, Roblox have recently released spatial voice chat. This feature is currently in developer beta and slowly rolling out to all players via age verification. See more here: https://blog.roblox.com/2021/09/introducing-age-verification/ We recently made a community poll to see how people felt about this change and a lot of you seem to be in favor for trying voice chat on The Wild West so I've gone ahead and enabled it for all new servers. Here's some key notes about spatial voice chat: Spatial voice chat allows you to speak to other players within proximity to your character in-game. Don't like someone? You can mute specific people in the Roblox menu by pressing the escape key. You can mute yourself either via the Roblox menu or by clicking the microphone icon above your head. This is not global voice chat; only proximity! I don't want voice chat! Don't worry! If you're an introvert like me, this feature is completely opt-in. You won't be able to hear or speak to other players if you do not have this setting enabled on your Roblox privacy settings. So, if you want to be left alone, you can turn this off at any time. Important Note Not all players currently have voice chat; this has been released for about a month now under a private developer beta and is slowly rolling out over the next few weeks via age verification for all users 13+ on the platform.
